&gt; Welcome!
&gt;
&gt; Here are some suggestions.  First, get the Kingsley Read manual in PDF
&gt; form if you don&#39;t have it already.
&gt;
&gt; There is a Junior QS example paragraph which uses all the letters.  With
&gt; key in hand, decode it like a cryptogram, sounding out all the words.
&gt; It will be slow going the first time.
&gt;
&gt; Next, pick a few consonants and a few vowels from the list.  Try to
&gt; write all the words you can think of that use those sounds.  It would
&gt; be a good game to play with your son! Then pick another handful and
&gt; repeat.
&gt;
&gt; Then, try to read the harder examples in the manual and do some practice
&gt; writing.  It&#39;s a great way to keep a diary which few humans can read...
&gt;
&gt; Finally, if you have your fonts in order, you can correspond with others
&gt; on this list.  We&#39;d all love to read your work.
&gt;
&gt; Have fun,
&gt;  - Mitch
&gt;
